entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
Signals whether to explosive rockets onto the belts. This is the case only when the ship is travelling between the Shattered Planet and System Edge or System Edge and Aquilo, or when there are insufficient yellow rockets available.
1 = Put explosive rockets onto the belt (will also tell the other inserter to remove yellow rockets from the belt)

entities.name: constant-combinator
entities.player_description: Acts as a filter for the next combinator to output only yellow Gun Turret ammo > normal or all red Gun Turret ammo.

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description: Outputs all type of Gun Turret ammo to the next combinator.

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description: Ensures that the inserter always takes the ammo where amount in stock is higher than stack size

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
Signals whether to throw yellow rockets onto the belts. This is the case only when the ship is not travelling between the Shattered Planet and System Edge or System Edge and Aquilo, or when there are insufficient explosive rockets available.
1 = Put yellow rockets onto the belt (will also tell the other inserter to remove explosive rockets from the belt)

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description: Checks which items are above a threshold (one threshold valid for everything) and signals to throw it out.

entities.name: selector-combinator
entities.player_description: Acts as a filter for excess items to be thrown out into void.

entities.name: selector-combinator
entities.player_description: Decides whether to throw iron ore, carbon or nothing on the belt, depending on how much is already on the belt. If more than 40 iron ore and carbon is on the belt, filter points to nothing. If 30 iron ore, 42 carbon is on the belt, filter points to iron ore....

entities.name: constant-combinator
entities.player_description: Acts as a filter to the connected combinator, to choose either iron ore, carbon (if <= 40 is on the belt) or nothing (if > 40 is on the belt).

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
Signals to slow down if velocity exceeds a certain threshold, checked per each section (low / medium / high / no danger area). Also signals to slow down if threshold set for area is not exceeded, BUT low amount of ammo or low amount of resourced to produce ammo.
1 = Slow down

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description: If slow and peaceful space, speed up

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
Signals to speed up if in non-peaceful space, either if we have enough thruster fuels or the velocity is below a certain threshold or if ammo stock is high or enough resources to produce ammo.
1 = Speed up

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
Low danger if moving between Aquilo and friendly solar system.
1 = Low danger

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
Medium danger if moving from Aquilo to System Edge or arriving at Edge.
1 = Medium danger

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
Highest danger if moving between System Edge to Shattered Planet or arriving at Shattered Planet.
1 = High danger

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
No danger if moving between Nauvis, Gleba, Vulcano and Fulgora.
1 = Peaceful area

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
Either enough thruster fuels and water, as well as electricity storage OR medium amount of fuels, but enough resources to produce more thruster fuels.
1 = Enough thruster fuel (resourced)

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description: Outputs 1 if enough resources to produce rockets and coal.

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
High ammo stock if enough Gun Turret ammo, enough explosive rockets, enough rockets in total and enough Railgun Ammo.
1 = High ammo stock

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
Very high ammo stock if a lot of Gun Turret ammo, enough explosive rockets, a lot of rockets in total and enough Railgun Ammo.
1 = Very high ammo stock

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
Low ammo stock if low amount of explosive rockets, low amount of red Gun Turrent ammo, low amount of Railgun ammo, low iron plates amount and low amount of rockets in total (OR not enough resources to produce more rockets).
1 = Low ammo stock

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
Critically low ammo stock if very low amount of rockets in total, very low amount of total Gun Turrent ammo or very low amount of Railgun ammo.
1 = Very low ammo stock

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
Signals whether it's safe to travel on with relatively high requirements.
1 = Continue your journey

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
Signals whether it's safe to travel on with minimum conditions.
1 = Continue your journey
